Although the number of experts was 12, they were carefully selected based on predefined scientific criteria to guarantee sufficient knowledge, practical experience, and diversity in relevant fields, including environmental management, renewable energy, sustainable development, and carbon emission reduction policy. This selection process aimed to capture the perspectives of key stakeholders and experienced practitioners relevant to carbon emission reduction in Quang Ngai province. The expert panel collectively met the practical requirements for ANP analysis, as the pairwise comparison matrices were evaluated for consistency (

    C
    R
    &lt;
    0.1

), hence confirming the reliability of their assessments. This approach ensured that the derived priorities of strategies were scientifically robust and reflective of real-world considerations.
